<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>try eqtraders, got all you need recipe and stat wise, this recipe is cobalt drake hide, drake egg oil, 2 velium boning and a belt pattern, past 115, tailoring becomes very very very very hard, and these velium stud/boning using armors are thought to be past 200 skill for triv<BR>
<BR>
Truebud Sureskinner(54 druid 128 tailor on saryrn server)</font></td></tr></table>
<BR>
<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Prexus Tailor</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2001-04-11 11:36:26</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>This tailored armor Triv's at about 230 no less. And due to the skill gap (from 130 to 230 there is nothing to tailor to raise the skill for these 100points) these are going to be very rare and difficult to make. Drake Eggs are a less than 1% foraged item in Skyshrine, to make the Oil you need 130ish Brewing, the Boning is a pain also because its made from the Non-stackable Velium blocks they are heavy and you have to kill alot of orcs in CC to get them. Add to that you need to be a Master smith to make them I forget the skill level but its over 100 =/ <BR>
<BR>
After you got all the stuff together which takes many many hours if not days you put all your eggs into one basket and pray you don't suck as much as you think you do. <BR>
<BR>
BTW good luck on the Cobalt drakes they are a pain in the ass to kill and when you get close to killing one finially, those little booger otttermen like to come KS you).<BR>
<BR>
You really want a PC on this item it take a Master of Trades to complete.<BR>
<BR>
Honestly I would not let this item outta my hands for less than 8k, depending on failures, If I had alot of Fails I would probally only take trades on it.<BR>
<BR>
If you think you can get a better deal try to find someone who knows how to make it and still wants to TRY.. </font></td></tr></table>
